         <pb n="1"/>
         <head><title>Songs from a Free Space*

         Alone</title>
				<persName>Deborah Hiller</persName>
			</head>
         <lg>
            <l>She who walks alone and dreams</l>
				<l>will remain lonely.</l>
				<l>She who sleeps with her pillow</l>
				<l>only dreams of her pillow as partner.</l>
				<l>But she who sits in her cell,</l>
				<l>and writes</l>
				<l>will master this world.</l>
			</lg>
         <p>*From <title>Songs from a Free Space/Writings by Women in Prison</title>, edited by Carol Muske and Gail Rosenblum, New
				York, n. d.
			</p>
      </body>
